The Piet Retief Magistrate's Court. JOHANNESBURG - Eight men charged with the murder of Sifiso Thwala and Musa Nene will continue their bail application in the Piet Retief Magistrate's Court. 
The accused face murder attempted murder and kidnapping charges. READ: Presidency urged to intervene in Mkhondo Thwala and Nene were allegedly tortured and killed after they got stuck with a tyre puncture near the Pampoenkraal farm. Farm owners accused them of livestock theft. Three of the accused are being charged with the murder of the Coka siblings.